Gaming, Lodging, & Leisure Weekly Matters

We address the following key issues affecting Gaming, Lodging & Leisure stocks: 1) Investors are asking about CHDN, WYNN, FUN; 2) Cruise and Theme parks show strong summer; 3) Previewing CHDN NDR; expect discussions on Derby Growth and NH property; 4) NY Weekly OSB Hold Down 100bps WoW on Strong Handle; Fanatics Handle Up Huge on Low Hold. 5) Join our prediction markets expert call on September 15th.

Investors asking about CHDN, WYNN and FUN performance. In a relatively quiet week, the performance of these three stocks, \(- 0.3\%\) \(+10.9\%\) and \(- 12.9\%\) for the week, respectively, was a focus of investors. In our view, FUN is impacted by the void of information on leadership and guidance, which challenges a reasonable support level. Meanwhile, the updates from Macau suggest GGR could be up \(13 - 16\%\) in August, which we believe is driven by several forces, but nonetheless implies \(\sim 20\%\) + growth in EBITDA which is not reflected in estimates. The start- off to September would be critical in whether there is follow- through on the strength in a seasonally quiet month ahead of October Golden Week. Finally, the weakness in CHDN is driven by any obvious trend, with monthly data points coming in solidly, most notably in VA. However, the closing of Salem casino property could bring incremental capital spending, which we believe could be weighing on the shares.

Travel Tapestry. Jef's collaborative analysis of travel data shows continued strength in cruise lines with pricing accelerating through the summer. In addition, theme parks have shown positive trends recently, highlighted by increased web visits and app user activity rising. On the other hand, US Hotel RevPAR continues to slide and inbound travel weakness has continued. Our note HERE.

CHDN NDR Preview. JEF is hosting CHDN's Sr. Mgt. team in New York on Wednesday 9/3. We expect commentary on the status of capital projects for the Derby, update on the recently acquired project in Salem, NH and progress towards reducing bank covenant leverage below 4.0x. CHDN has provided a clear growth pathway through 2026 from a combination of anticipated Derby projects and an improving outlook in VA/KY. Our latest note HERE.

NY Weekly OSB Hold Down 100bps WoW on Strong Handle; Fanatics Handle Up Significantly Again on Another Low Hold. Statewide NY OSB trends continued from last week, with hold down 100bps WoW to \(6.3\%\) on handle up \(82\%\) YoY (again driven by Fanatics' handle nearly 1,000% YoY). Note- reports indicate that last week Fanatics took a single wager of over \(100M\) , which very well could have been repeated this week. Despite the strong handle, Fanatics hold fell another 160bps WoW to just \(0.2\%\) , holding \(441K\) on \(231M\) in wagers. Aside from Fanatics, hold increased WoW for all operators exFLUT, which held just \(8.9\%\) on the week (its first sub- DD hold since April). QTD, FLUT still leads in hold at \(12.4\%\) , while BetMGM and DKNG are #2 and #3 at \(10.6\%\) and \(10.5\%\) , respectively.

Join our Prediction Markets Expert Call. On September 15th, we're hosting Dan Wallach, Sports Attorney and Founder of Wallach Legal, LLC to discuss the legality of prediction markets in the US. We'll review the legality of prediction market operators offering sports contracts without state gaming licenses, the potential outcomes of active litigation against Kalshi and thoughts on OSB players entering the space. Register for our call HERE.

Underperform - Describes securities that we expect to provide a total return (price appreciation plus yield) of minus \(10\%\) or less within a 12- month period. The expected total return (price appreciation plus yield) for Buy rated securities with an average security price consistently below \(10\) is \(20\%\) or more within a 12- month period as these companies are typically more volatile than the overall stock market. below \(\) 10\(, the expected total return (price appreciation plus yield) is plus or minus 20% within a 12 - month period.
